IRON MOUNTAIN — The schedule for the area junior high girls basketball league tournament has been set. Teams that participate in the league are Iron Mountain Norway Kingsford Niagara Florence North Dickinson Forest Park and West Iron.

The seeded tournament is single-elimination format and will beginning with preliminary games on Monday and Tuesday. The two A Division championship games will be held on Thursday in Crystal Falls at Forest Park School while the two B Division championship games will be held at Norway High School on the same night.

— 7th Grade A: 1. Kingsford vs. 4. Iron Mountain Tuesday at Iron Mountain 5:30 p.m.;

2. Forest Park vs. 3. Niagara Monday at FP in Big Gym 6:30 p.m.

— 7th Grade B: 5. WIC vs. 8. Florence Monday at FP in the Elementary Gym 6:30 p.m.;

6. Norway vs. 7. North Dickinson Monday at Niagara 5:30 p.m.

— 8th Grade A: 1. Forest Park vs. 4. WIC Monday at FP in Big Gym 5:30 p.m.;

2. Norway vs. 3. Florence Monday at FP in Elementary Gym 5:30 p.m.

— 8th Grade B: 5. Iron Mountain vs. 8. North Dickinson Tuesday at Iron Mountain 6:30 p.m.; 6. Niagara vs. 7. Kingsford Monday at Niagara 6:30 p.m.
